summary:
Self-motivated, enthusiastic, ambitious, outgoing student of Business Economics at the University of Groningen with an interest in finance, accounting, management, marketing, and data analysis. This university has helped me develop myself and discover a new passion for me in the fields of finance, management, and marketing. During my studies, I faced many obstacles, which I managed to overcome by reminding myself of my values and what I work towards. Through the program, I was able to learn analytical-reasoning, efficient problem-solving, and great organizational abilities. The courses in this program have taught me budgeting, strategizing, attention to detail, and the importance of communication. I am ambitious in pursuing a management, marketing, or finance career within a socially responsible business environment with proactive characteristics and strategy.
My voluntary work has helped me discover myself and my ambitions at a very young age. I have been able to develop excellent leadership, communication, and adaptability skills by participating in numerous projects and organizations.

Proficient in Excel, Word, and Google Sheets, WordPress. Intermediate-level Stata. 
Speak fluent English (C1 level), and Macedonian (mother tongue).
Beginner-level Turkish. 
Silver medalist Olympiad for Mathematical Finance and Actuary - OFMA
Led multiple projects and organized numerous events successfully.
